{"title":"Moots Announces Womble Slider Single Speed w/ UDH Option","link":"https://bikerumor.com/moots-womble-slider-single-speed-udh/","date":1683639777000,"content":"<p>News from Steam Boat Springs, Colorado, <a href=\"https://moots.com/\" target=\"_blank\">titanium bicycle manufacturer</a> Moots Cycles introduces their <a href=\"https://moots.com/bikes/mountain/womble/\" target=\"_blank\">new</a> Womble Slider single-speed. The new Womble Slider is based on their iconic hardtail MTB, the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/moots-womble-widens-tire-clearance-tubing-for-aggressive-new-titanium-hardtail/\" target=\"_blank\">Womble</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-rear-dropout-and-brake-1-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-rear-dropout-and-brake-1-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Moots Womble Slider rear dropout and brake\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-rear-dropout-and-brake-1-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-rear-dropout-and-brake-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-rear-dropout-and-brake-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-rear-dropout-and-brake-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-rear-dropout-and-brake-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-rear-dropout-and-brake-1-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-rear-dropout-and-brake-1-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This new single-speed uses Paragon Machine Works’ sliding rear dropout, and will have an optional dropout that makes the Womble Slider UDH compatible as well.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-side-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-side-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Moots-Womble-Slider-front-side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-side-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-side-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-side-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-side-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-side-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-side-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-side-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Photo c. Moots Cycles</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-back-side-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-back-side-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Moots-Womble-Slider-back-side\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-back-side-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-back-side-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-back-side-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-back-side-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-back-side-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-back-side-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-back-side-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Moots says this bike is for the “ultra-purist rider that wants a simplified connection to the bike and trail.”</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Being based on the Womble’s progressive geometry, the Womble Slider is deemed a “modern-classic” mountain bike at home on single-track, XC trails, backroad gravel, and bike packing… making it a versatile titanium hardtail.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-end-scaled-e1683581716860.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-end-scaled-e1683581716860-800x440.jpg\" alt=\"Moots-Womble-Slider-front-end\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-end-scaled-e1683581716860-800x440.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-end-scaled-e1683581716860-297x163.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-end-scaled-e1683581716860-120x66.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-end-scaled-e1683581716860-768x422.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-end-scaled-e1683581716860-1536x845.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-front-end-scaled-e1683581716860-2048x1126.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Designed to take a 140mm travel front suspension fork, this clean, stripped-down, titanium single-speed is built with proprietary double-butted top and down tubes. Moots says it’s stiff under hard pedaling, making for a perfect single-speed platform. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Giving the rear end room for up to 29 x2.6″ tires, the curved seat tube also allows for the rear end to stay tucked for that out-of-the-saddle single-speed charge. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>“Single speeding strips away all distractions other than pedal, coast, and carry momentum. Read the trail, and find the flow; the smiles will follow”. </em></p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Womble Geometry</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Geometry.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"182\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Geometry-800x182.jpg\" alt=\"Moots Womble Geometry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Geometry-800x182.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Geometry-297x67.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Geometry-120x27.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Geometry-768x174.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Geometry-1536x349.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Geometry.jpg 1651w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Frame Specs</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Head Tube: 44mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bottom Bracket: 73mm threaded</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Seatpost: 30.9</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rear End Spacing: 148 thru-axle</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Post Mount Disc Size: 160mm or 180mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Max Tire: 29×2.6″</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Water Bottle Locations: 2 (small size has 1)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Ring Capacity: 32t</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Derailleur Hanger: Replaceable</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-Boone-rear-ti-cog-scaled.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-Boone-rear-ti-cog-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Moots-Womble-Slider-Boone-rear-ti-cog\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-Boone-rear-ti-cog-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-Boone-rear-ti-cog-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-Boone-rear-ti-cog-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-Boone-rear-ti-cog-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-Boone-rear-ti-cog-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-Boone-rear-ti-cog-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/Moots-Womble-Slider-Boone-rear-ti-cog-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>Boone titanium 18t cog</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Retail and Build Options</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Retail:</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Frame only: $4975 (w/brushed finish)</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Single Speed Build Option</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Full SS Build: $9999 (w/brushed finish)</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>FRAME: Womble Singlespeed w/sliding Dropouts</li>\n\n\n\n<li>FORK: RockShox Pike Ultimate 140mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>HEADSET: White Industries</li>\n\n\n\n<li>STEM: ENVE M6</li>\n\n\n\n<li>BAR: ENVE M6 780MM</li>\n\n\n\n<li>DROPPER POST: RockShox Reverb AXS 150MM</li>\n\n\n\n<li>CRANK: White Industries W/32T chainring</li>\n\n\n\n<li>CHAIN: SRAM XO1</li>\n\n\n\n<li>COG: Boone titanium 18t</li>\n\n\n\n<li>BRAKES: SRAM G2 RSC</li>\n\n\n\n<li>WHEEL SET: Astral Boost Outback Carbon W/ White Industries CLD Hubs</li>\n\n\n\n<li>TIRES: MAXXIS Rekon 29 X 2.6</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SADDLE: WTB Silverado Fusion/ TI Rails</li>\n\n\n\n<li>GRIPS: OuryV2</li>\n\n\n\n<li>CAGES: Moots/SilcaTI x2</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Moots</p>\n\n\n\n<p> </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/moots-womble-slider-single-speed-udh/\">Moots Announces Womble Slider Single Speed w/ UDH Option</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"8c355e0f0032f6e0b8c363eab6507eca661cdfd779b10c497d447cf42d5af642","category":"Cycling"}